columns = ["Oil_USD", "Wheat_USD_1", "Gasoline_RUS_USD", "Gasoline_AUD_USD", "USD_RUB", "Key_rate_RUS", "Key_rate_AUD"]
def income_label(value, minValue, maxValue):
  return {
    value < ((maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue):  'Very low',
    ((maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue) <= value < (2*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue):  'Low',
    (2*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue) <= value < (3*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue):  'Medium',
    (3*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue) <= value < (4*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue):  'High',
    (4*(maxValue - minValue)/5 + minValue) <= value: 'Very high'
  }[True]
In [ ]:
for i in columns: 
  max = df[i].max()
  min = df[i].min()
  df[i] = df[i].apply(
      lambda x: income_label(x, min, max))
